Package: CropRotationViz
Title: Interactive Tool for Crop Rotation Sequence Analysis and Visualization
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Franz", "Schulze", , "franz.schulze@geo.uni-halle.de", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: An interactive Shiny application for analyzing and visualizing crop rotation 
    sequences from agricultural field data. The package provides tools for processing 
    field geometries, analyzing crop rotations across multiple years, and creating 
    interactive visualizations. Key features include field intersection analysis, 
    support for multiple spatial file formats (SHP, GeoJSON, FlatGeobuf, GeoPackage), 
    and customizable visualization options. Designed for agricultural researchers and 
    practitioners working with spatiotemporal crop rotation data.
